Xfce is a fast and lightweight desktop environment that is both
visually appealing and easy to use.

As of >= XFCE 4.8 many GNOME dependencies are required.  Follow the
build order below for assistance.

A python script has been included to auto-download the lastest
XFCE tarballs. To use download.py:

  $ ./download.py


Package to remove before running xfce.SlackBuild:

  - thunar-archive-plugin
  - thunar-volman
  - xfce
  - xfce4-notifyd
  - xfce4-power-manager
  - xfce4-screenshooter
  - xfce4-taskmanager


Dependency build order:

  1. GConf (optional):
       http://slackbuilds.org/repository/13.37/libraries/GConf/
  
       1. ORBit2:
            http://slackbuilds.org/repository/13.37/libraries/ORBit2/
  
  2. libsoup:
       http://slackbuilds.org/repository/13.37/libraries/libsoup/
       
       1. libproxy (optional):
            http://slackbuilds.org/repository/13.37/libraries/libproxy/
  
  3. udisks:
       http://slackbuilds.org/repository/13.37/system/udisks/
       
       1. sg3_utils:
            http://slackbuilds.org/repository/13.37/libraries/sg3_utils/
       
       2. libatasmart:
            http://slackbuilds.org/repository/13.37/libraries/libatasmart/
  
  4. upower (optional, needed for xfce4-power-manager):
       http://slackbuilds.org/repository/13.37/system/upower/
  
  5. glade3 (optional):
       http://slackbuilds.org/repository/13.37/development/glade3/
  
  6. gvfs:
       http://slackbuilds.org/repository/13.37/system/gvfs/ 
  
       1. gnome-disk-utility (optional):
            https://github.com/jgeboski/SlackBuilds/tree/master/gnome-disk-utility/
            ../gnome-disk-utility/
            
            1. gnome-common:
                 http://slackbuilds.org/repository/13.37/development/gnome-common/
            
            2. libunique:
                 http://slackbuilds.org/repository/13.37/libraries/libunique/
